# Redesign skills — carlesdelolmo.com

When the task involves any visual change to this project, use the skill system in `.llm/skills/`.

## Entry point

Always start with `.llm/skills/00-redesign-skill-router.md` to identify the correct skill.

## Skills

- `00-redesign-skill-router.md` — Decides which skill to load
- `01-redesign-orchestrator-en.md` — Broad redesign coordination
- `02-visual-tokens-carles-2026.md` — CSS tokens and color palette
- `03-global-components-redesign.md` — Navbar, footer, buttons, cards, forms
- `04-page-sections-redesign.md` — Hero, homepage, service pages, blog
- `05-safe-redesign-workflow.md` — Safe execution for large changes
- `06-redesign-qa-check.md` — QA before PR or merge

## Hard rules

- Never work directly on `main`.
- Do not change SEO, schema, metadata, routes, analytics, cookies or legal content unless explicitly requested.
- Do not change copy or headings when the task is visual.
- Do not introduce colors outside the approved palette.
- Do not use visible gradients.
- Do not add visual libraries without approval.
- Keep changes small and reviewable.

## Approved visual direction

Warm, clear, technical, young, professional, boutique, strategic.
Not: AI-themed, generic SaaS, neon, cyberpunk, template-like.
